__data__.text:
[Opening Scene: Dicha smiling at the camera]

Dicha:  
"Hey everyone! Welcome back to Tech and English with Dicha! Today, we're diving into five essential 
words every AI and ML developer should know. Let’s get started!"

---

[Cut to a text overlay of the first word: "Algorithm"]

Dicha:  
"First up, we have Algorithm. This is a step-by-step procedure for solving problems. In AI and ML, 
algorithms help us process data and make predictions. Super important!"

---

[Cut to the second word: "Model"]

Dicha:  
"Next is Model. Think of it as a mathematical representation of a system. In machine learning, we train 
models on data to recognize patterns and make predictions. They can be anything from a simple linear 
regression to complex neural networks!"

---

[Cut to the third word: "Training"]

Dicha:  
"Now, let’s talk about Training. This is the process where we feed data into our models so they can learn. 
The goal? Minimize errors and improve accuracy. It's like teaching a child until they get it right!"

---

[Cut to the fourth word: "Overfitting"]

Dicha:  
"Next, we have Overfitting. This is when a model learns the training data too well, capturing noise 
instead of the real patterns. The result? It performs poorly on new data. We definitely want to avoid that!"

---

[Cut to the fifth word: "Feature"]

Dicha:  
"And finally, we have Feature. This is an individual measurable property used as input for our models. 
Choosing the right features is crucial for a model's success, and that's where feature engineering comes in!"

---

[Closing Scene: Dicha smiling at the camera]

Dicha:  
"So there you have it! Five key terms every AI and ML developer should know. Let me know in the comments 
which word was your favorite! Don’t forget to like and follow for more tech and language tips. See you next time!"

---

[End Screen: Subscribe and follow prompts]  

Dicha:  
"Tech and English with Dicha—where learning meets innovation!"
